frameDefinitions: A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
These are words describing a basic commercial transaction involving a Buyer and a Seller exchanging Money and Goods, taking the perspective of the Buyer.
A Lessor who owns some Goods allows a Lessee to use the Goods temporarily in exchange for Money.
A Payer gives up (or potentially gives up) the use of an Asset (generally money) in order to achieve an Intended_event.
This frame involves Buyers paying Money for Goods.
frameExamples: We are <t>renting</t> our apartment from a kind man named Tom.
Abby bought a car from Robin for $5,000.
It 'll <t>cost</t> Sandra's parents fifty grand a year for her to attend that school.
I <t>paid</t> her $50 for a video game.
